		<div id="listing-items">
			
							
						
						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Agricultural-Development-under-a-Changing-Climate-Opportunities-and-Challenges-for-Adaptation" title="Agricultural Development under a Changing Climate: Opportunities and Challenges for Adaptation" alt="link">Agricultural Development under a Changing Climate: Opportunities and Challenges for Adaptation</a></h2>

	
					<p>This report reviews the major effects of climate change on the agricultural sector. It examines the causes of vulnerability and suggests a range of potential options and investment opportunities for supporting adaptation efforts and building adaptive capacity. This report primarily focuses on appropriate strategies for adapting to climate change impacts that are projected to occur over the next one to two decades, although several issues covered in this report are important for long-term adaptation needs as well. This report also describes opportunities for linking adaptation and mitigation, and it discusses the importance of mainstreaming adaptation into development.</p>
							<p><span class="date">12/01/2012</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Agricultural-Development-under-a-Changing-Climate-Opportunities-and-Challenges-for-Adaptation">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
</p>
						
						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/ReSAKSS-Quarterly-Newsletter-Autumn-2011" title="ReSAKSS Quarterly Newsletter, Autumn 2011" alt="link">ReSAKSS Quarterly Newsletter, Autumn 2011</a></h2>

	
					<p>The Regional Strategic Analysis and Knowledge Support System (ReSAKSS) provides accessible, high-quality analysis, data, and tools to agricultural practitioners, researchers, policymakers, and development professionals to promote evidence-based decision-making, improve the awareness of the role of agriculture for development, close knowledge gaps, promote dialogue among stakeholders, and facilitate the review and adoption of best practices associated with the Comprehensive Africa Agriculture Development Programme (CAADP) and other leading agricultural development initiatives in Africa. In this issue, one will find details of the assistance provided to ECOWAS, summary of the Conference on Ag productivity and food security, links to reports on the tracking of intra-regional trade of ag inputs, on the monitoring and evaluation of the sector targets, and to discussions on the price policy responses in Eastern and Southern Africa.</p>
							<p><span class="date">12/01/2012</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/ReSAKSS-Quarterly-Newsletter-Autumn-2011">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
</p>
						
						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/World-Bank-s-Agriculture-and-Rural-Development-Department-Quarterly-newsletter-December-2011" title="World Bank’s Agriculture and Rural Development Department Quarterly newsletter, December 2011 " alt="link">World Bank’s Agriculture and Rural Development Department Quarterly newsletter, December 2011 </a></h2>

	
					<p>The World Bank’s Agriculture and Rural Development (ARD) Department produces a quarterly online publication containing abstracts of recent ARD papers and descriptions of key programmes and events. The newsletter is intended to contribute to the collective efforts of poverty alleviation by sharing information and exchanging knowledge. Featured stories in this issue include: ‘Call to Action’ on Climate-Smart Agriculture at COP17 in Durban (South Africa), and the ‘Science in Action’ initiative. Also of note are new ARD publications such as: Economic and Sector Work, ARD Discussion Papers, Partnership Publications, ARD Notes and Quick facts on gender and agriculture, the Global Food Price Crisis Response Program (GFRP).</p>
							<p><span class="date">12/01/2012</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/World-Bank-s-Agriculture-and-Rural-Development-Department-Quarterly-newsletter-December-2011">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
