<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/ScienceAfrica-Volume-17-August-September-2011" title="ScienceAfrica, Volume 17, August–September 2011" alt="link">ScienceAfrica, Volume 17, August–September 2011</a></h2>

	
					<p>This is the <a href="http://www.wfsj.org/files/file/resources/documents/ScienceAfrica/sia17.pdf" target="_blank">first part </a>of a special report on biotechnology in Kenya. Volume 17 of ScienceAfrica reports on Kenya's parliamentary debate over GMO's and the country capacity to deal with modern agricultural biotchnology, high-level support for biotech by politicians in the region, and the link between medical clinics and biotech research centres.</p>
